Positions.name: CEO
Positions.description: The CEO is the highest-ranking executive in a company, responsible for making major corporate decisions, managing overall operations, and providing strategic direction to achieve organizational goals.

Positions.name: COO
Positions.description: COO stands for Chief Operating Officer and is responsible for overseeing the day-to-day operations and business activities of a company to ensure the effective execution of strategies and achieve organizational goals.

Positions.name: Project Manager
Positions.description: A Project Manager is responsible for planning, organizing, and overseeing the successful execution of projects, ensuring they are completed on time, within budget, and meeting the project's objectives.

Positions.name: Tech Lead
Positions.description: A Tech Lead is a senior technical role responsible for guiding and overseeing a team of developers, providing technical direction, making architectural decisions, and ensuring the successful delivery of software projects.

Positions.name: CFO
Positions.description: The Chief Financial Officer (CFO) is responsible for overseeing the financial operations and strategies of an organization, including financial planning, reporting, budgeting, and managing financial risks.

Positions.name: Backend Developer
Positions.description: A Backend Developer is responsible for developing and maintaining the server-side applications, databases, and APIs that power web and mobile applications.

Positions.name: CTO
Positions.description: The CTO (Chief Technology Officer) is responsible for overseeing and guiding the organization's technology strategy and ensuring the effective implementation of technological solutions to achieve business goals.
